member.name: HTTP_BYTE_RANGE
member.summary: TheHTTP_BYTE_RANGE structure is used to specify a byte range within a cached response fragment, file, or other data block.

member.name: HTTP_BYTE_RANGE.StartingOffset
member.summary: Starting offset of the byte range.

member.name: HTTP_BYTE_RANGE.Length
member.summary: Size, in bytes, of the range. If this member is HTTP_BYTE_RANGE_TO_EOF, the range extends from the starting offset to the end of the file or data block.
